---
import MainLayout from "../components/MainLayout.astro";

const canonicalPath = "/advisory";
const title = "Advisory";
const summary =
  "Retained or project-based decision support for automation, robotics, and industrial AI markets.";
---

<MainLayout canonicalPath={canonicalPath} title={title} summary={summary} seoTitle="Advisory | Autonomy Bridge">
  <article class="max-w-[780px] mx-auto px-6 py-12 md:py-16">
    <header>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-4">Advisory</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mb-8">
        Retained or project-based decision support for automation, robotics, and industrial AI
        markets.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800">
        Autonomy Bridge provides advisory support for teams making automation, robotics, and
        industrial AI decisions where the cost of being wrong is high.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800 mt-4">
        The work starts with the actual constraint. Not a packaged methodology. Not a generic
        consulting process. The objective is to define the decision, test the assumptions, and
        produce an output that can be used.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-neutral-200">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-4">Who this is for</h2>

      <h3 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Warehouse operators and 3PL executives</h3>
      <p class="text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800">
        Used when vendor claims, pilot results, or deployment economics need independent evaluation
        before capital is committed.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold mb-2 mt-8">Investors and diligence teams</h3>
      <p class="text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800">
        Used when a robotics company, automation vendor, or logistics asset needs a more realistic
        view of market position, unit economics, and scale assumptions.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold mb-2 mt-8">Robotics and automation vendors</h3>
      <p class="text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800">
        Used when go-to-market strategy, pricing logic, segmentation, or buyer-side positioning is
        not landing with the market.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-neutral-200">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-4">Engagement models</h2>
      <p class="text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800">
        Autonomy Bridge works in two formats:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 mt-4 text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800">
        <li>
          Retainer advisory for recurring decisions that need continuity, structured analysis, and
          direct analyst access
        </li>
        <li>
          Project-based advisory for a defined question, output, and timeline
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800 mt-4">
        A project can stand alone. It can also serve as the diagnostic that defines a narrower
        retainer.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-neutral-200">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-4">What the work covers</h2>
      <p class="text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800">Typical scopes include:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 mt-4 text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800">
        <li>warehouse automation ROI and utilization analysis</li>
        <li>vendor economics and competitive comparison</li>
        <li>workflow constraint mapping</li>
        <li>market entry and segment sizing</li>
        <li>robotics commercial diagnostics</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-neutral-200">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-4">What this is not</h2>
      <p class="text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800">
        Autonomy Bridge does not implement systems, manage deployments, build software, or fill
        embedded operator roles.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800 mt-4">
        The work is analytical and commercial. Not implementation consulting.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-neutral-200">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-4">
        How engagements start
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800">
        Every engagement starts with a direct scoping conversation. If there is a fit, scope is
        defined in writing before work begins.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800 mt-4">
        That scope includes:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 mt-4 text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800">
        <li>the decision being supported</li>
        <li>the output to be delivered</li>
        <li>the analytical boundary</li>
        <li>timeline</li>
        <li>fee basis</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-neutral-200">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-4">
        Start a conversation
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800">
        Every engagement starts with a 15-minute scoping call to define the problem.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mt-6">
        <a
          href="/contact"
          class="inline-flex items-center rounded-md bg-neutral-900 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-white hover:bg-neutral-700 transition-colors"
        >
          Book 15-min scoping call &rarr;
        </a>
        <a
          href="/case-studies"
          class="inline-flex items-center rounded-md border border-neutral-300 bg-white px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-neutral-900 hover:bg-neutral-50 transition-colors"
        >
          See Case Studies &rarr;
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</MainLayout>
